    "last_audit": "2026-04-05",
    "audit_changes": [
      "LA: follow_up for Sch III/II changed async → sync. Louisiana requires sync AV for ALL controlled substance encounters, not only first visits. Category renamed SYNCHRONOUS_REQUIRED.",
      "NJ: Sch II follow_up value normalized from non-standard 'in_person_every_3_months' → 'in_person_required'. Frequency captured in constraints as 'quarterly_in_person_frequency'. Previous value broke orchestrator switch statement silently.",
      "TX: Moved 'async_ok_if_seen_within_90_days' from first_visit constraints to follow_up constraints where it semantically belongs. Added to follow_up constraints block which was previously empty.",
      "AL: Removed 'licensed_staff_at_originating_site' constraint. Alabama Act 2018-509 eliminated originating-site staffing requirement for general telehealth. Constraint was Medicaid CMS-origin and inapplicable to private-pay DTC model. Pending AL counsel confirmation.",
      "CA: Retained first_visit sync for Sch III. B&P 2290.5 permits async good-faith exam but sync is the conservative standard-of-care position for controlled substance prescribing. Revisit with legal counsel before downgrading to async.",
      "WA: No changes. Permanently-sync follow-up is conservative but defensible per MQAC guidance.",
      "NY: No changes. In-person-first for all scheduled substances confirmed correct.",
      "FL: No changes. Sch II blocked, Sch III async with DOH registration confirmed correct."
    ],
    "notes": "DEA telemedicine flexibilities extended through Dec 31, 2026. Schedule III includes testosterone (injectable + oral). All other MOH services are non-scheduled. service_id keys use hyphen format — normalize on intake (see router.py)."
  },
